{
  "texts": [
    "Compared with OFDM, OTFS is more suitable for high mobility scenarios such as vehicular networks due to its high tolerance to time and frequency dispersion [104].",
    "Moreover, the advantages of high spectrum efficiency and reduced peak-to-average power ratio (PAPR) make OTFS a promising candidate for ISAC [49,105].",
    "A pioneering work was done by Gaudio et al. [106], and the sensing capability of the OTFS waveform was verified.",
    "Then they extended it to the multiantenna case [107], where the multi-antenna ISAC-BS adopted hybrid beamforming for target tracking.",
    "Moreover, Yuan et al. [108] investigated the ISAC-supported OTFS transmission for vehicular networks and proposed an effective beamforming prediction scheme."
  ]
}